<subSubSection id="459F57F10B71F47B5AA340B6F0EA83D5" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="multiple">
<paragraph id="E521A990B1F6A841B450E2E3BC88F8DB" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Taxon classification Animalia Hymenoptera Chrysididae</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DC2506255C042DE14393BC4D889BA594" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8B056134088770180C3262444D002A25" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicName id="41BA6A08DC7BEB5C916EDBCC4626BB5D" authority="Shuckard, 1837" authorityName="Shuckard" authorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Chrysis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chrysis ruddii" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruddii">Chrysis ruddii Shuckard, 1837</taxonomicName>
Fig. 96
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="952D1AAC3ACAF77F205B3D33E621D4B5" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="6CD52A1E76C91AEEB85974E314DA65E3" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
<taxonomicName id="0A684C59F3A51581CDB4989292100C8A" class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Chrysis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chrysis Ruddii" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="Ruddii">
<pageBreakToken id="0C127105F0D5717EFAEF72EA17397BA6" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" start="start">Chrysis</pageBreakToken>
Ruddii
</taxonomicName>
Shuckard, 1837: 163.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="018AC94090878B663B0B1A69677B069B" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
<taxonomicName id="FF4AB4F1D5F7023302FE58B8EB1B6857" class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Chrysis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chrysis auripes" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auripes">Chrysis auripes</taxonomicName>
Wesmael, 1839: 175.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1B3C047BD3A4762CA682D1B68448DEA1" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B4E3930A789270D7673803A275932233" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FE130BA5F2C4DE699A3532F701AFDEF0" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
Length 7-10 mm. As in most other species of the 
<taxonomicName id="EEA56CA14F5D978A6A8AE623BE5A1CDB" class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Chrysis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chrysis ignita" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ignita">Chrysis ignita</taxonomicName>
group, the head and mesosoma are mainly blue or green and the metasoma is dorsally golden red. However, the mesoscutum, mesoscutellum and propodeum, and often also tegulae and mesopleuron, have extensive golden or coppery reflections in the female. The sternites and legs are ventrally coppery red in both sexes. The punctation of the tergites is very fine and dense throughout, punctures being of uniform size (Fig. 96). In the male, the punctation is often somewhat sparser, and therefore it is more easily confused with other similarly coloured species of the 
<taxonomicName id="EC07CBEB81D0DA92E6B1429ADE741266" class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Chrysis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chrysis ignita" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ignita">Chrysis ignita</taxonomicName>
group (e.g. 
<taxonomicName id="81C2AE049195827C0D5FA287F3006338" class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Chrysis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chrysis subcoriacea" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subcoriacea">Chrysis subcoriacea</taxonomicName>
). The combination of a short pronotum (length less than one fourth of its width), non-metallic F1 and coppery red sternites should be used to distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="977FFECF947220F7AFE40C96D88EE8A4" class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Chrysis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chrysis ruddii" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruddii">Chrysis ruddii</taxonomicName>
males reliably from other species of the group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="27F5A3E19E456F66D56DD013EAC18E50" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="FB1C1B7D1837D753C9C66073F267F716" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E682AD60158A88F0A853FA48B03461AF" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
Denmark, Estonia, Finland, Latvia, Lithuania, Norway, Sweden. Relatively common. - West Palearctic: Europe, Asia Minor (
<bibRefCitation id="EDF84B7C446DC0CBBBC0723EA852AA5F" author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Veroeffentlichungen aus dem Natur-Museum Luzern" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" pagination="1 - 139" title="Die Goldwespen der Schweiz." volume="9" year="1997">Linsenmaier 1997</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5C37395985BADD8671E0D0DA3FC0F3F2" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="biology">
<paragraph id="435FB96A741B38D88EC7450345B2AE8D" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5BE9FFF93CDC8B6998D8FA93D1212FD1" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
Habitat: dry meadows, rocky outcrops, cliffs, clay banks, forest margins. Adults occasionally visit flowers of 
<taxonomicName id="C70DF8A89F81387CA2C70204E793D950" authority="Steud., 1840" authorityName="Steud." authorityYear="1840" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Heteroptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heteroptera" order="Apiales" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Apiaceae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="546B4EA8FFACC91A744D4D09C5665A18" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Heteroptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Heteroptera" order="Hemiptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Euphorbiaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="5939EEA8D1C101D50A707D60538E48B4" author="Heinrich, J" journalOrPublisher="Nachrihten des Naturwissenschaftlichen Museums der Stad Aschaffenburg" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" pagination="1 - 28" title="Beitrag zur Hymenopteren-fauna des westlichen Unterfranken. 1. Teil, Chrysididae." volume="71" year="1964">Heinrich 1964</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5B7D111D92532D57AF94813E2CEAB0DE" author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Veroeffentlichungen aus dem Natur-Museum Luzern" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" pagination="1 - 139" title="Die Goldwespen der Schweiz." volume="9" year="1997">Linsenmaier 1997</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F5399A6E8744B9E5A1B9DBD272EA88E5" author="Rosa, P" journalOrPublisher="Giornale Italiano di Entomologia" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" pagination="79 - 90" title="Alcune osservazioni sulle relazioni tra Vegetazione e Crisidi (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae) in Italia." volume="11" year="2004">Rosa 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="A44956274FE3D77F8FF7390E6DAC7889" author="Rosa, P" journalOrPublisher="- Pierre, Aosta" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" title="I Crisidi della Valle d'Aosta (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae). Monografie del Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali, 6. St." year="2006">2006</bibRefCitation>
). Flight period: mid-May to early August. Host: primarily 
<taxonomicName id="36D627FEE3626FF7141065A02D5C8301" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Ancistrocerus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ancistrocerus oviventris" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oviventris">Ancistrocerus oviventris</taxonomicName>
(Wesmael) (
<bibRefCitation id="34A3B6355DE52BA07DFE9D81B6B237C2" author="Berland, L" journalOrPublisher="Paul Lechevalier, Paris" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" title="Hymenopteres vespiformes. III. (Cleptidae, Chrysidae, Trigonalidae). Faune de France, Vol. 34." year="1938">Berland and Bernard 1938</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="C4EF0B305F3EF51E9EDAAB7DAE6003B2" author="Banaszak, J" journalOrPublisher="Katalog Fauny Polski" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" pagination="1 - 52" title="Zlotolitki Chrysididae." volume="26" year="1980">Banaszak 1980</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="029E8BD0A22C6C68EA1F0ADC38EFE1BB" author="Morgan, D" journalOrPublisher="Royal Entomological Society of London, London" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" title="Cuckoo-wasps, Hymenoptera, Chrysididae. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects, Vol. 6, Part 5." year="1984">Morgan 1984</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8F96ABA79B460EEC7B2B0929ACAB1528" author="Kunz, PX" journalOrPublisher="Beihefte zu den Veroeffentlichungen fuer Naturschutz und Landschaftspflege in Baden-Wuerttemberg" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" pagination="1 - 188" title="Die Goldwespen (Chrysididae) Baden-Wuerttembergs. Taxonomie, Bestimmung, Verbreitung, Kartierung und Oekologie. - Mit einem Bestimmungsschluessel fuer die deutschen Arten." volume="77" year="1994">Kunz 1994</bibRefCitation>
, our own obs.), but possibly also 
<taxonomicName id="C0EA657D36EB2737221CF4E22C68ED8D" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Ancistrocerus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ancistrocerus parietum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parietum">Ancistrocerus parietum</taxonomicName>
(Linnaeus), 
<taxonomicName id="14749E844B84531F271AAA56EF2162E0" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Ancistrocerus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ancistrocerus scoticus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scoticus">Ancistrocerus scoticus</taxonomicName>
(Curtis), species of 
<taxonomicName id="B9810D9710553BF6778161E42F272722" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Eumenes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eumenes" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eumenes</taxonomicName>
Latreille, 
<taxonomicName id="5BFEC5B64721D3B304335376196D1F00" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Odynerus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Odynerus spinipes" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinipes">Odynerus spinipes</taxonomicName>
(Linnaeus) and 
<taxonomicName id="14A9FD78FD7F321F4DA8E70306ABB1C3" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Odynerus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Odynerus reniformis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reniformis">Odynerus reniformis</taxonomicName>
(Gmelin) (
<taxonomicName id="F0415FEE0F4F23D5086BB65BACDFC6C5" family="Vespidae" lsidName="" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" rank="family">Vespidae</taxonomicName>
) (Forsius in 
<bibRefCitation id="51EFADE37722F6ABAFDC30041CC25C15" author="Trautmann, W" journalOrPublisher="Uschman, Weimar" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" title="Die Goldwespen Europas." year="1927">Trautmann 1927</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E5EF4E742707F09B1968E7DB5BBF083E" author="Berland, L" journalOrPublisher="Paul Lechevalier, Paris" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" title="Hymenopteres vespiformes. III. (Cleptidae, Chrysidae, Trigonalidae). Faune de France, Vol. 34." year="1938">Berland and Bernard 1938</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="A232CD13A0A53EF9549045159CF474F0" author="Banaszak, J" journalOrPublisher="Katalog Fauny Polski" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" pagination="1 - 52" title="Zlotolitki Chrysididae." volume="26" year="1980">Banaszak 1980</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="27FD77D376AA0E4112046FB902CA27D9" author="Kunz, PX" journalOrPublisher="Beihefte zu den Veroeffentlichungen fuer Naturschutz und Landschaftspflege in Baden-Wuerttemberg" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" pagination="1 - 188" title="Die Goldwespen (Chrysididae) Baden-Wuerttembergs. Taxonomie, Bestimmung, Verbreitung, Kartierung und Oekologie. - Mit einem Bestimmungsschluessel fuer die deutschen Arten." volume="77" year="1994">Kunz 1994</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="56EDDED39F1E83E02569B9D9734CE994" author="Martynova, KV" journalOrPublisher="Entomological Review" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" pagination="472 - 485" title="Chrysidid wasps (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae) - parasites of eumenine wasps (Hymenoptera, Vespidae: Eumeninae) in Crimea." url="10.1134/S0013873815040090" volume="95" year="2015">Martynova and Fateryga 2015</bibRefCitation>
, our own obs.). Records stating solitary bees (e.g. 
<taxonomicName id="0DAF0888063F95B8C7AB0014EC3A21E8" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hoplitis adunca" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adunca">Hoplitis adunca</taxonomicName>
(Panzer) and 
<taxonomicName id="5958DC688701D26C0B68039722681B15" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hoplitis anthocopoides" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anthocopoides">Hoplitis anthocopoides</taxonomicName>
(Schenck)) as hosts are doubtful, as bees differ significantly in their biology from the vespid hosts.
</paragraph>
